dcterms:description: The CelebA dataset contains over 200k images with various resolutions that can be square-cropped to 128×128. It is used for training the Pioneer network to achieve high-quality image reconstruction and synthesis.
dcterms:title: CelebA

dcterms:creator: T. Karras
T. Aila
S. Laine
J. Lehtinen
dcterms:description: CelebA-HQ is a subset of CelebA containing 30k images that have been improved and upscaled to 1024×1024 resolution. It is used for training the Pioneer network to generate high-quality images.
dcterms:title: CelebA-HQ

dcterms:creator: F. Yu

T. Funkhouser
J. Xiao
dcterms:description: The LSUN dataset contains images of various categories in 256×256 resolution or higher. The bedrooms category is often used for testing generative models.
dcterms:title: LSUN

dcterms:description: Cifar-10 is a dataset containing 60,000 labeled images at 32×32 resolution, spanning 10 classes. It is used for comparison in the paper.
dcterms:title: Cifar-10
